parameters: As you move closer to the singer, you feel another presence.
Looking over, you see a vaguely familiar cloaked figure, leaning against a
crate. Watching the singer. Listening to the song.
"You shouldn't interrupt them singing. Wait until they're done."
The man's voice is rough.\| Tired.\| Familiar.
I thought this song was just for me.
"That's a difficult question to answer.\| At least I can say this:\| I\| am\| me."
I thought this song was just for me.
"Did you, now? Perhaps it is. Perhaps me being here is a mistake. But it matters little.\. I am here."
"You should let her tell you that herself."
You decide to leave the familiar stranger to himself, and instead focus on the song.
It's a familiar song. A song you shouldn't know.
An unknown language, yet the meaning of the words pass through your mind like sand in your hands.
Hope, as if it's the end of the world.
Despair, as if you waited your whole life for this moment, this second.
A burning throat. Frozen fingers. Screams of hatred whispered lovingly into your ears.
You can't hear the song anymore. You can't see the singer anymore. You aren't you anymore. You are-
Aaaaahhhhh it feels great getting to sing my heart out in these things. Viva la lucid dreaming!!!\n<Singer>
The emotions fade. The hole remains empty. The Answer is forgotten. Once again...
Hmhmhm, I probably have some time before I wake up. Guess I can take a walk around the city and plan my day. I wonder if I'll see that guy again...\n<Singer>
A lone figure stands at the end of a short pier. Even though you've followed the song meant for you this far, she's not looking in your direction.
No, her gaze is fixed upon that distant horizon.
